# Rule Authoring Quality
- One concern per rule file; split mixed concerns.
- Keep rules short, explicit, and action-oriented.
- Prefer scoped `globs` and avoid unnecessary `alwaysApply: true`.
- Reference canonical project files instead of copying large examples.
- Update rules when repeated agent mistakes appear; avoid edge-case bloat.
